Omni, Vinen already pointed out how completely off-base this comment was....but come on.  I'm willing to listen to yoru commentary and try to understand your opinion, but making flat-out inaccurate comments that show you are clearly on one side of the spectrum here...just isn't convincing in the least.  Lets try to meet somewhere in-between okay?  And lets agree on a few facts.  In every other expansion prior to PoP, you could pretty much count the raid-zones on one finger.  Vinen added a few that I disagree with (PoFear, PoHate, ToV) purely because an expansion or so later, even casual raiders or single-groupers were able to access the content.  With the institution of PoP and GoD there is now a significant amount of content locked behind raid encounters.  Can we at least get that far before we start the arguing?  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.therambler.net/images/sigs/vigdissig3.jpg" border="0" />
