                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Sure, I can give you that.
<br />

<br />
Zones like Hate, Fear, VP etc, whetted the whistle of the raider.  PoP gave them almost an entire expansion to play with.....
<br />

<br />
But look what happened.  Sometime after release (and it was quite awhile, but I forget the actual timespan), tier 3 was opened up to anyone of a specific level.  Xp groups now live in BoT and HoH (well...is more soloers there I think).
<br />

<br />
When it's all said and done, a person who doesn't raid, attains at least level 62, and never makes the first step towards progression has PoI, PoJ, PoD, PoN, PoS, PoV, HoH, BoT, and CoD to play around in.  That's 9 zones.  The progressive raider gets seven more zones.  Tactics, Solro, Water, Fire, Earth, Air, and Time.  Also there is a one-groupable alternate quest to gain access to Tactics.  So really, as today's game stands, there are 6 "raider only" zones.  That's 6/16 for those keeping track.  About 38%.  Sure,  it's more raid content than Kunark, but raid population has also grown since that time.
<br />

<br />
LDoN....well, I can't call that a raiding expansion.  Can you?
<br />

<br />
LoY?  Hate's Fury for maybe a couple mobs I guess.  Otherwise, entirely one groupable.
<br />

<br />
GoD....I'm not going to attempt to list all the zones, as I don't know them all.  I'll say what I do know.  As far as one-groupable xp zones the non-raider has access to Natimbi, Qinimi, Riwwi, Ferubi, Barindu, Vxed, Tipt (or can you only get there after completing Vxed?  I really don't know), and 4 instanced sewer trials.  Following those for the raider (oh God, I *am* going to try to list them) there's Kod'Taz, Inktuta-something, Txevuu or some such, Uqua, Qvic, Tacvi, and Ikkinz, I believe.
<br />

<br />
11 non-raider zones/7 raider zones.  Someone please correct me because I'm 99% sure I'm wrong on the GoD zones, I just don't care to look it up right now.
<br />

<br />
Assuming that I am correct however, that's 7/18.  Again, 39%.  Quite in line with PoP.
<br />

<br />
All of these zones have their "raid targets" sure, but didn't Sebilis, Chardok, HS, Velk's and Kael have them as well?
<br />

<br />
Yes, raid content has increased because the number of raiding guilds has increased.  Do I believe this game is solely focused on raiding?  No, I don't.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.allmond.net/images/kain1.gif" border="0" />
<br />
