                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The problem with your numbers is they include the 'newbie zones'.  So they don't apply to the 'hardcore non-raider' that is having the most difficulty and about whom most of the current posts are being written.
<br />
Also, some zones are just plain worthless.  A few masochists might become faithful devotees of the zones, but places like kc, velks, bot,  poe are heavily populated for good reason.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">When it's all said and done, a person who doesn't raid, attains at least level 62, and never makes the first step towards progression has PoI, PoJ, PoD, PoN, PoS, PoV, HoH, BoT, and CoD to play around in. That's 9 zones. The progressive raider gets seven more zones. Tactics, Solro, Water, Fire, Earth, Air, and Time.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
For a level 65, you can take poi, poj, pon, and pod off the list as they are generally too low level.  That  makes the ratio look much worse.
<br />

<br />
God has:
<br />

<br />
accessible: Natimbi (newbie), Qinimi (newbeish), Barindu, Ferubi, Riwwi, SewerPlant, SewerPool, SewerCrematory, SewerLair.  I wouldn't rank any of these as a terribly good place to farm/xp.
<br />

<br />
accessible with some single group stuff: Vxed, Tipt, Kod'Taz, Yxxta,  Ikkinzgroup1, Ikkinzgroup2, Ikkinzgroup3.  This is the more solid portion of the expansion for a 'hardcore non-raider' and the only real barrier to success is that of gear and group class composition.
<br />

<br />
raidonly: Ikkinzraid1, Ikkinzraid2, Ikkinzraid3, Ikkinzraid4, Uqua, Qvic, Inktu'ta, Txevu, Tacvi
<br />

<br />
I think god has gone back in the right direction at least regarding raid/group content.  With the exception of qvic and possibly txevu after the release of oow  (atm farm/xp there outside of a raid would be far too dangerous and considering there aren't many drops you would have to be truly masochistic to try it even after oow), the list of 'raidonly'  is a list of zones in which only raid events occur so the non-raider wouldn't have any desire to go there or be missing anything by being rendered unable to do so by flags.  That at least is a step in the right direction from the pop model of raiders having access both to raid zones and superiour grouping zones as they were both in the same zones.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=648415" target="_blank" class="postlink">Londo Mollari</a>
