<br />

<br />
I don't think you are understanding my point. 
<br />

<br />
First off, I'm not convinced that raid content has increased.  I think many of the previous expansions contained raid content, with the exception of the very first EQ release prior to the planes being put in (you'll note that I'm not counting LoY at all.  You can lump that into the nonraider content but let's be honest here:  not even hard core nonraiders use that content.  It sucks.  After a couple weeks of exploring, I chalk the entire expansion up to a great map maker).  Even then, though, hell, Guk was a raid.  Raid content has stayed pretty much the same.  The _difference_ is that now non-raiders cannot access it _at all_.  As such, even if we have a really bad ass group and we get level 70 with OoW....it means jack because we'll STILL never see the Plane of Fire or Txavu.  Hey, at least in earlier expansions I could zone into ToV and see the dragons and I could check out lower Guk ooc spam while groups tried to take out the named.  
<br />

<br />
Right now?  I think we are playing completely different games and while nonraider content may be available for the raiders should they choose or desire to see it, nonraiders will never get the opportunity to see almost a third of the zones in PoP and GoD.  Maybe they can't beat that content in the current expansion, or even the next expansion, but it would be nice if eventually they could at least try.  Furthermore, we shouldn't just assume it's for the encounters or the loot.  Many of us just like to experience new content - well nonraiders do too.  Anyone can get into VP (the old one) because Trak is virtually soloable.  Anyone can get into ST because Zlandicar/Klandicar are single-groupable.  I wager that with level 70 anyone can get into VT as Emp will be two-groupable.  But no matter how many times you tap your little red shoes together, RZ is not going down with two groups, and neither is the Keeper of the Alter (even assuming you kill the Guardians of Glorification, Nixki, or Tunik spirit).   See, I don't have a problem with raid content and raid targets.  I have a problem with it being locked behind arbitrarily difficult encounters.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.therambler.net/images/sigs/vigdissig3.jpg" border="0" />
<br />
