                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You stole my name.  By the laws of the Couro Prido, I challenge you to the Morago, Llondo Mollari!
<br />

<br />
Anyway, even the single groupable gear available in ikkinz isn't of the quality of the raid loot available now.  There is already single groupable loot far better than some old raid loot from e.g. tov.  At some point, even raid gear has to be surpassed by single groupable gear to keep up with mudflation.  The question is where to put that line in each new expansion.  Should single group gear in oow be ssra level, vt level, ep level, time level?  All of this is raid gear but eventually single groupable gear has to surpass it or eventually non-raiders would fall so far behind they wouldn't even be viable players (some might say this is the current case).
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">there is NO single group content in a current expansion that can be even remotely comparable in difficulty to a raid encounter. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Depends on the raid.  The first day we ran into ferubi as a guild we killed weaponsmith with half the raid not paying attention.  On the other hand, it took us weeks to get a single group past ikkinz1.  Just because in the past most single group encounters haven't compared in difficulty to raids doesn't mean they couldn't be designed as such in the future.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=648415" target="_blank" class="postlink">Londo Mollari</a>
<br />
 Tholuxe Paells</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
