Had I realized when I registered that there was another Londo posting here I would have registered under the name of main, who is a wizard, which I'm sure you would also recognize:  Lenieer.
<br />

<br />
However I will gladly accept the challenge as any true Centauri would!!!
<br />

<br />
Let me restate my opinion as I do agree that eventually single groupable gear will outshine yesterdays raid gear, and I don't have issue with that.
<br />
At this point in time, Plane of Time is STILL fairly prestigious (hell Elementals is still fairly prestigious) and we are still at a point where I would guess that only 20-25% or less of the server wide population is flagged for it.  To me no single group content should drop anything near what drops in Plane of Time....YET.  While not the best gear currently available it is still ELITE gear in terms of stats and focus effects.  As of NOW the only place you can get better gear is post Uqua in GoD.
<br />

<br />
There is some single group content in GoD that drops elemental quality if not better loot and i'm a little iffy on whether I think thats proper, but at least those mobs aren't pushovers.
<br />

<br />
Currently my guild is working on the PITA that is Uqua...and I sure as heck better not see anything as good as Uqua and better level loot on single group content for a LONG time...because the only way to create Uqua level difficulty stuff for a single group is to make it so hard that NO single group could survive it without Time/GoD Gear....there is simply no way to gimp the content for casual geared people without making it a complete joke to everyone else (the gear differences are too large).  If you haven't been to Uqua yet you can't possiby undertand what I mean by that, and if you have you know exactly what I'm talking about.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Llondo Mollari
<br />
57th Enchanter
<br />
Bristlebane Server
<br />
Ring of Valor
